prompt: Dim flicker-lit computer lab, CRT glow on sweating faces: middle-aged Del in wrinkled ’80s suit, terrified girl’s eyes behind his wire specs; beside him, teenage girl’s body frozen mid-pose, your avatar face hologrammed above her head split-screen laughing/guilty; endless message boards cascade behind like digital rain, cursor blinking “BINGO—”

Slowly pan back: the three stand apart, Venn circles now separate on the CRT, monitors show Del’s banned profile beside your intact count and her single anonymous post; flickering lights steady, the room feels emptier, swap rig powers down.
